es and related symptoms. | Product Specifications and Features: | Minimum sample required: Only 0.5 µL blood sample is needed, thus causing minimal pain while drawing blood | 5-depth adjustment: The device provides 5 depth adjustment options to select as per different needs of individuals | Internal Vibration Control System: This system helps in the comfortable drawing of blood | Tri-beveled tips: The tips of the lancet device are tri-bevelled and electro-polished for minimal pain and maximum comfort | Smart Spring mechanism: Ensures a smooth and easy process while drawing out blood | Reading time: 5 seconds | Compatible With: All round lancets | Directions for Use: Remove the lancing device cap by rotating it counterclockwise Insert a new lancet firmly into the lancet carrier Secure the body of the lancet and twist the cover to remove Place the lancing device cap back on the device and rotate clockwise to secure Select the level of skin penetration using the 5 options in the adjustable cap Hold the lancing device in one hand and use the other hand to pull the handle back until a click is heard, indicating the lancing device is ready. Release the sliding handle to return it to its original position Position the lancing device cap firmly against the finger and/or the desired area to be punctured, then press the trigger to fire Remove the lancing device cap by repeating step 1 Once the adjustable cap is removed, hold the body of the lancet and firmly stick the lancet needle into the cover. Remove the lancet from the carrier and discard it in an appropriate biohazard container | Safety Information: Read the label carefully before use Keep out of reach of children Avoid any physical damage Store in a clean and dry place Check the strips are within their expiry date Make sure to wash and dry your hands before testing | Quick Tips: Do not squeeze the finger when taking a blood drop sample. | Frequently Asked Questions: | What lancets can be used with this device? All round lancets are compatible with this device. | How to adjust the depth of penetration? The penetration depth can be adjusted using the adjustable cap, which offers 5 levels. 1-2 for soft or thin skin 3 for average skin 4-5 for thick or calloused skin | Are lancets provided with the device? No. The lancets are not included in the package and need to be purchased separately.','','','Control D Lancing Device Glucometer White Control D Lancing Device Glucometer White Testing blood glucose is an essential part of managing diabetes. This lancing device help measure blood glucose levels quickly, accurately, and comfortably. The device has a 5-depth adjustment, a comfortable grip, and an internal vibration control system (IVCS) for comfortable testing at home. It is used to obtain whole capillary blood for glucose testing.','','','','Remove the lancing device cap by rotating it counterclockwise | Insert a new lancet firmly into the lancet carrier | Secure the body of the lancet and twist the cover to remove | Place the lancing device cap back on the device and rotate clockwise to secure | Select the level of skin penetration using the 5 options in the adjustable cap | Hold the lancing device in one hand and use the other hand to pull the handle back until a click is heard, indicating the lancing device is ready. Release the sliding handle to return it to its original position | Position the lancing device cap firmly against the finger and/or the desired area to be punctured, then press the trigger to fire | Remove the lancing device cap by repeating step 1 | Once the adjustable cap is removed, hold the body of the lancet and firmly stick the lancet needle into the cover. Remove the lancet from the carrier and discard it in an appropriate biohazard container','','Read the label carefully before use | Keep out of reach of children | Avoid any physical damage | Store in a clean and dry place | Check the strips are within their expiry date | Make sure to wash and dry your hands b