dles mounted on top are synonymous with quality. Needle Size: 24G Salient features of Dispovan 3ml syringe With 24G Needle : Barrels are made of nontoxic, medical-grade polypropylene compatible with any medication. The tip of the barrel is of two types – luer mount and luer lock. Both have a 6% luer taper as per ISO:594. Plungers are made of nontoxic, medical-grade polypropylene compatible with any medication. Gaskets are made of natural rubber which is chemically inert and compatible with medication for short term contact drug delivery application. Safety information: Before use, check the integrity of the sealing of the pack. Do not attempt to re-sterilize and reuse.','','','Dispovan Syringe 3ml with Needle 24G Dispovan 3ml syringe With 24G Needle is manufactured as per IS:10258/ ISO:7886-1. Ribbon packaged, dispo van syringes with needles mounted on top are synonymous with quality. Needle Size: 24G Salient features of Dispovan 3ml syringe With 24G Needle : Barrels are made of nontoxic, medical-grade polypropylene compatible with any medication. The tip of the barrel is of two types – luer mount and luer lock. Both have a 6% luer taper as per ISO:594. Plungers are made of nontoxic, medical-grade polypropylene compatible with any medication. Gaskets are made of natural rubber which is chemically inert and compatible with medication for short term contact drug delivery application. Safety information: Before use, check the integrity of the sealing of the pack. Do not attempt to re-sterilize and reuse.','','','','','','Before use, check the integrity of the sealing of the pack. Do not attempt to re-sterilize and reuse.','','','','901-902, Narian Manzil , 23, Barakhamba Road New Delhi-110001 (India)','ADD TO CART','India','','','','',0.00,0,0.00,0.00,0.00,NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','2026-05-17 07:49:18','2026-05-17 07:49:18',NULL,NULL,NULL),(165,'BD Emerald 3ml Syringe','Healthcare Devices','Diabetes Monitoring','','100 syringes','box of 100 syringes',900,'','NO','','BD Emerald 3ML Syring: Salient features of BD Emerald 3ML Syring: Green Rubber. Bold Scale Markings to accurate dose. Clear Barrel for visualization of fluid. Textured Thumb Press to reduce slippage during administration. Safety information: keep out of the reach of children. Do not use the product if found damaged.','','','','','','','','','keep out of the reach of children. Do not use the product if found damaged.','','','','Plot- 1 Investate Bawal , Haryana - 123 501','ADD TO CART','India','','','','',0.00,0,0.00,0.00,0.00,NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','2026-05-17 07:49:18','2026-05-17 07:49:18',NULL,NULL,NULL),(166,'Recombigen Glucometer Plastic Round Lancets','Healthcare Devices','Diabetes Monitoring','','100 lancets','box of 100 lancets',140,'','NO','','Recombigen Glucometer Plastic Round Lancets A blood lancet, or simply a lancet, is a small medical implement used for capillary blood sampling. A blood lancet is similar to a small scalpel but with a double-edged blade or needle. Lancets are used to make punctures, such as a fingerstick, to obtain small blood specimens. Blood lancets are generally disposable. | Uses: A blood lancet, or simply a lancet, is a small medical implement used for capillary blood sampling. | Product Specifications and Features: Electro-polished needle, which is an electrochemical finishing process that removes a thin layer of material from a metal part in stainless steel or similar alloys for an ultra-clean finish and reduction in friction Ergonomic design with easy twist star cap The tri-bevel tip ensures painless prick Packed under hygienic conditions and is packed thin that you will hardly feel it going through your skin | Compatible With: Lancing devices. | Directions for Use: Put the blood lancet into the lancing device and remove the protective cap before use After use, insert the tip of the blood lancet into the protective cap and place it in the waste bucket | Safety Information: Read the label carefully before use Store in a cool and dry place, away from sunlight Keep out of reach of children Single-use lancet | Quick Tips: Never use a lancet that has been used by someone else Each lancet is intended for single, one-time use | Frequently Asked Questions: Can a lancet be reused? No. Lancets are for single use only. It is strongly advised to always discard a lancet after every use. Use a new sterile lancet every time you test to help avoid infection and improve comfort and performance. How often should you test your blood glucose? If you have type 1 diabetes, you may need to check your blood glucose levels several times a day (pre and post-meals, before and after exercise) or as advised by your doctor. Whereas, if you have type 2 diabetes, the frequency of monitoring the sugar levels might be based on the severity of the condition, which can be several times a day, once a day, or thrice a week. Therefore, it would be best to consult your doctor about how often you should test your blood glucose.','','','Recombigen Glucometer Plastic Round Lancets Recombigen Glucometer Plastic Round Lancets','','','','Put the blood lancet into the lancing device and remove the protective cap before use | After use, insert the tip of the blood lancet into the protective cap and place it in the waste bucket','','Read the label carefully before use | Store in a cool and dry place, away from sunlight | Keep out of reach of children | Single-use lancet Quick Tips: Never use a lancet that has been used by someone else | Each lancet is intended for single, one-time use Frequently Asked Questions: Can a lancet be reused? No. Lancets are for single use only. It is strongly advised to always discard a lancet after every use. Use a new sterile lancet every time you test to help avoid infection and improve comfort and performance. How often should you test your blood glucose? If you have type 1 diabetes, you may need to check your blood glucose levels several times a day (pre and post-meals, before and after exercise) or as advised by your doctor. Whereas, if you have type 2 diabetes, the frequency of monitoring the sugar levels might be based on the severity of the condition, which can be several times a day, once a day, or thrice a week. Therefore, it would be best to consult your doctor about how often you should test your blood glucose.','','','','#98 Badli Industrial Estate, Phase 2, Near Sector 18, Rohini DTC Bus Depot, Delhi 110042','ADD TO CART','India','','','','',0.00,0,0.00,0.00,0.00,NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','2026-05-17 07:49:18','2026-05-17 07:49:18',NULL,NULL,NULL),(167,'Infant Mask','Healthcare Devices','Dr Morepen','','1 Unit','packet of 1 Unit',242,'','NO','','The infant mask device is designed to ease the process of administering inhaled bronchodilators and anti-inflammatory drugs to the lungs. It packs a metered dose inhaler (MDI) and a Zerostat VT Spacer for infants and children below three years of age. With the help of baby mask, the child can easily take the medicine while breathing through his mouth. The attachment of the mask to spacers also provides small tidal volumes and low inspiratory flow rates in babies and young children. The newborn mask is also useful for those who have difficulty in maintaining a good lip seal on the mouth piece of the metered dose inhaler (MDI). Directions of use: Uncover the Infnat mask device Apply the baby mask to the child Fill it with medicine Let the infant suck it with the inhaling breath Clean the mask after use with cold or lukewarm water use under medical supervision.','','','','','','','','','','','','','Cipla House, Peninsula Business Park, Ganpatrao Kadam Marg, Lower Parel, Mumbai-400013','SOLD OUT','','','','','',0.00,0,0.00,0.00,0.00,NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','2026-05-17 07:49:18','2026-05-17 07:49:18',NULL,NULL,NULL),(168,'Nipro Syringe with Needle 10ml (21G,1)','Healthcare Devices','Diabetes Monitoring','','100 syringes','box of 100 syringes',1950,'','NO','','Nipro Syringe with N