ter to upload all blood glucose readings to an electronic diary | Indication: Diabetes Mellitus | Compatible With: Contour Plus test strips and Contour Diabetes app | Directions for Use: Insert the test strip with the grey square end facing the meter (this will automatically turn on the meter) Immediately add blood to the test strip Your result is displayed (after marking as fasting, before/after a meal or no note) | Safety Information: Read the label carefully before use Keep out of reach of children Avoid any physical damage Store in a clean and dry place Check the strips are within their expiry date Make sure to wash and dry your hands before testing | Quick Tips: Every time you start to use a new box of test strips, make sure to calibrate your meter Do not squeeze your finger when taking a blood drop sample | Frequently Asked Questions: | What is the smartLIGHT feature? And what do the colours mean? The smartLIGHT feature on the CONTOURPLUS ONE meter gives instant feedback on your blood glucose results. It immediately identifies your results as above, below or within the target range to help you make decisions. This feature can be switched off if you prefer not to use it. Green = within the target Amber = above target Red = below target | What is Second-Chance sampling? If your first sample is insufficient to take a blood glucose reading, Second-Chance sampling lets you apply more blood to the same strip instead of using a new one. This may help you avoid pricking your finger again and waste fewer strips (and lancets).','','','Contour Plus One Blood Glucose Monitoring System with Contour Plus Blood Glucose Test Strip 25 Free Contour Plus One Blood Glucose Monitoring System with Contour Plus Blood Glucose Test Strip 25 Free can be used for quantitatively measuring glucose in blood samples. It is simple to set up, easy to use and results in 5 seconds.','','','','Insert the test strip with the grey square end facing the meter (this will automatically turn on the meter) | Immediately add blood to the test strip | Your result is displayed (after marking as fasting, before/after a meal or no note)','','Read the label carefully before use | Keep out of reach of children | Avoid any physical damage | Store in a clean and dry place | Check the strips are within their expiry date | Make sure to wash and dry your hands before testing Quick Tips: Every time you start to use a new box of test strips, make sure to calibrate your meter | Do not squeeze your finger when taking a blood drop sample Frequently Asked Questions: What is the smartLIGHT feature? And what do the colours mean? The smartLIGHT feature on the CONTOURPLUS ONE meter gives instant feedback on your blood glucose results. It immediately identifies your results as above, below or within the target range to help you make decisions. This feature can be switched off if you prefer not to use it. Green = within the target Amber = above target Red = below target What is Second-Chance sampling? If your first sample is insufficient to take a blood glucose reading, Second-Chance sampling lets you apply more blood to the same strip instead of using a new one. This may help you avoid pricking your finger again and waste fewer strips (and lancets).','','','','1st Floor, Bella Vista, Oswal Park Pokhran Road No-2, Majiwada Junction Thane (W) – 400 601 Maharashtra, India','ADD TO CART','Switzerland','','','','',0.00,0,0.00,0.00,0.00,NULL,'','','','','','','','','','','2026-05-17 07:49:18','2026-05-17 07:49:18',NULL,NULL,NULL),(174,'Vissco 2901 Dura Max Universal Grey','Healthcare Devices','Dr Morepen','','1 Walker','box of 1 Walker',3256,'','NO','','Vissco 2901 Dura Max Universal Grey It is a walker ideal for people who need additional support to maintain stability while walking. | Uses: It is ideal for people who need additional support to maintain stability while walking | Product Features and Specifications: Lightweight aluminium frame for a long life High-grade rubber shoes and rubbe